-- Est Media Falls to Record Low as Fourth-Quarter Loss Widens
-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 2012-04-10T07:59:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-10/est-media-falls-to-record-low-as-fourth-quarter-loss-widens.html
EST MEDIA Vagyonkezelo Nyrt., a
Hungarian entertainment company, fell to the lowest on record
after its fourth-quarter net loss widened.  The shares dropped 15 percent to 100 forint by 9:42 a.m. in
Budapest. The company reported a net loss of 1.5 billion forint
for the last three months of 2011, compared with a loss of 1.1
billion forint in the same period of 2010, according to a
statement to the Budapest Stock Exchange late on April 6. The
bourse was closed on April 6 and 9 for a public holiday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andras Gergely in Budapest at 
 agergely@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at 
 gserkin@bloomberg.net  